data.content:
Your `ReportGenerator` has several untestable statics. For the **file system calls** (`File.*`, `Directory.*`), the best approach is the **`System.IO.Abstractions`** NuGet package — it's battle-tested and provides a complete `IFileSystem` interface.

### Recommended approach

**1. Install the package:**

```
dotnet add package System.IO.Abstractions
```

For your test project, also add:

```
dotnet add package System.IO.Abstractions.TestingHelpers
```

**2. Inject `IFileSystem` into `ReportGenerator`:**

```csharp
using System.IO.Abstractions;

public class ReportGenerator(IFileSystem fileSystem)
{
    public string GenerateReport(string reportName)
    {
        // ...
        if (!fileSystem.Directory.Exists(outputDir))
            fileSystem.Directory.CreateDirectory(outputDir);

        var reportPath = fileSystem.Path.Combine(outputDir, $"{reportName}_{timestamp}.txt");
        fileSystem.File.WriteAllText(reportPath, content);
        // ...
    }
}
```

**3. Register in DI:**

```csharp
builder.Services.AddSingleton<IFileSystem, FileSystem>();
```

**4. Test with `MockFileSystem`:**

```csharp
var mockFs = new MockFileSystem();
mockFs.Directory.CreateDirectory("/tmp/reports");

var generator = new ReportGenerator(mockFs);
var path = generator.GenerateReport("Sales");

Assert.True(mockFs.File.Exists(path));
Assert.Contains("Sales", mockFs.File.ReadAllText(path));
```

---

### You also have other statics in that class

| Static | Best abstraction |
|---|---|
| `DateTime.UtcNow` | **`TimeProvider`** (built-in on .NET 10) — register `TimeProvider.System`, test with `FakeTimeProvider` from `Microsoft.Extensions.TimeProvider.Testing` |
| `Environment.GetEnvironmentVariable` / `MachineName` | Custom `IEnvironmentProvider` wrapper (no built-in exists) |
| `Console.WriteLine` | Custom `IConsole` or use `ILogger<T>` instead |

Want me to refactor `ReportGenerator.cs` to inject all of these, or focus on just the file system calls?
